===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|ic}} – originally {{zh-l|*圭}} and {{zh-l|*口}} in the oracle bone script. The top component mutated into {{zh-l|*士}} in Western Zhou bronze inscriptions.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s-kjit||happy; pleased}} (STEDT). Also compare {{cog|bo|སྐྱིད་པ||to be happy}} and {{cog|my|ချစ်||to love, to be pleased}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}, {{zh-ref|Hill, 2019}}).

Cantonese sense of “empty” arises from avoidance of {{m|yue|空|tr=hung{{sup|1}}|t=empty}}, which is homophonous to {{m|yue|凶||inauspicious}}.

The Taiwanese Chinese sense of “to sue” arises from avoidance of {{zh-l|告|gào|to sue}}, which is a typo form of it.

